description:
&lt;p&gt;Advert&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are recruiting for Band 5 Anaesthetic Nurses and Operating Department Practitioners to join our experienced teams in Paediatric/Obstetric and In-patient Theatres departments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About Us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Royal London Hospital is an internationally reputable Trauma Centre and Helicopter Emergency Medical Service (HEMS).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have 26 state-of-the art elective and emergency theatres, covering a variety of specialties and complex procedures:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hepto-billary, complex ENT, trauma &amp; orthopaedics, reconstructive orthopaedics, neurosurgery, complex vascular surgery, intervention radiology, maxilla facial surgery, robotic procedures, renal transplants, plastic reconstructive surgery, neonatal surgery, shared airway ENT, ophthalmic surgery, along with providing paediatric expertise to the major trauma service in South East of England&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We also cover outside areas in the hospital including endoscopy unit, radio-interventional suite, MRI/CT Scanner suites and our specialised staff work along the Trauma Team in Emergency Department’s Resuscitation area. This offers an opportunity to work with renowned Specialist Trauma Surgeons and Anaesthetists.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; We are also committed to providing ongoing professional and educational development as part of staff development and career progression.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About you – skills and experience required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be an enthusiastic and a motivated Registered Nurse or Operating Department Practitioner, with a passion for Trauma Care and with a commitment to own professional development, ideally with an experience of working in a busy theatre environment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be committed to developing your professional competence and building your skills portfolio through experiential learning and education to maximise your career prospects.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you seek a challenge, you will be joining our team at an important time of change as we continue our initiatives to improve our patients’ experience at Barts Health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Follow Team Peri-Op on Twitter @peri_team to find out more about us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Philip Dapaah, Senior Charge Nurse/ Anaesthetic Team Lead; Email: Philip.dapaah@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Philip Dapaah, Senior Charge Nurse/ Anaesthetic Team Lead; Email: Philip.dapaah@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
